 <strong>  COMMENT </strong>
      
      <br>  <br>

Dear, Mariam Markosyan I am from Azerbaijan, today I found this web-page and read most of the comments which made by school children and adults such as you. I wanna say that before I didnt know that there was an Azeri day in Arm school. As a young citizen of Aze, I can say that we also want peace, we wanna go back to occupied places. and can understand better than me that - if we wanna get something, both sides should make compromises. so I have a question for - what your country does for make peace? I really liked, when I saw that Arm children and adults want peace, but why you guys don't say that "we should give back Karabagh and 7 regions around Karabagh" ? none wants war! but we cant wait anymore, we keep dialogue with you guy more than 15 years. I hope you can understand me as educated and intelligent person. best regards: 	  
<br> <strong>Tural Mehtili | 01.03.2010 </strong>	  

